Imagine casino. asked play new type roulette. time , cost participating. rules simple: pick red option black option. choose red option, dealer give three-thousand dollars. pick black option, dealer spin wheel release ball. wheel weighted 80% chance getting four-thousand dollars 20% chance getting zero dollars. option choose? ?economic theorist, bet choose black option higher expected value. Expected values, \(EV\), calculated multiplying magnitude, \(x\), outcome probability, \(p\), occur. example, red option leads three-thousand dollars certainty. black option leads four-thousand dollars 80% chance (probability 0.8).\[\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\text{EV}(\text{Red}) &= x_{\text{Red}} \times p_{\text{Red}} \\
&= 3000 \times 1 \\
&= 3000 \\
\\
\text{EV(Black)} &= x_{\text{Black}} \times p_{\text{Black}} \\
&= 4000 \times 0.8 \\
&= 3200
\end{aligned}
\tag{2.1}
\end{equation}\]Looking expected values option calculated (2.1), see \(\text{EV}(\text{Red}) > \text{EV(Black)}\). Therefore, rational choice according classical economist choose black option.new type roulette presented prototypical example prospect – choice two options explicit probabilities outcomes – used investigate decision-making risk. prospect two options commonly denoted follows first option leads outcome \(x_a\) probability \(p_a\) second option leads outcomes \(x_b\) probability \(p_b\).\[\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\text{Option } &= (x_a, p_b) \\
\text{Option B} &= (x_b, p_b)
\end{aligned}
\tag{2.2}
\end{equation}\]Unless otherwise stated, alternative outcomes option assumed zero. , choosing Option choice receiving \(x_a\) probability \(p_a\) nothing probability \((1 - p_a)\).
